<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 4:35AM EDT  by NWS Louisville</headline>
<description>...Heat Index readings of 100 to 105 possible this afternoon...
August sun and a humid air mass will lead to elevated heat index
readings this afternoon, likely surpassing the century mark
generally along and west of Interstate 65.
If outside this afternoon, drink plenty of water and spend as much
time in the shade as possible. Do not leave children or pets
inside vehicles -- look before you lock!
Heat indices may be slightly higher tomorrow.</description>
